Name: 3-methylglutaconic aciduria
Definition: An organic acidemia that is characterized by elevated levels of 3-methylglutaconic acid and 3-methylglutaric acid in the urine.

Name: glutaric acidemia I
Definition: An organic acidemia characterized by impaired  lysine

Name: combined malonic and methylmalonic acidemia
Definition: An organic acidemia characterized by elevated levels of methylmalonic acid and malonic acid in body fluids typically resulting in developmental delay and failure to thrive in children and neurological symptoms in adults that has_material_basis_in homozygous or compound heterozygous mutation in ACSF3 on 16q24.3.

Name: propionic acidemia
Definition: An organic acidemia that involes a nonfunctional propionyl CoA carboxylase affecting conversion of aminio acids and fats into sugar for energy.

Name: methylmalonic acidemia
Definition: An organic acidemia that involves an accumulation of methylmalonic acid in the blood.

Name: isovaleric acidemia
Definition: An organic acidemia that disrupts or prevents normal metabolism of the branched-chain amino acid leucine.

Name: maple syrup urine disease
Definition: An organic acidemia that is caused by a deficiency of decarboxylase leading to high concentrations of valine

Name: obsolete metastatic malignant neoplasm to brain
Definition: An organic acidemia that is caused by a deficiency of decarboxylase leading to high concentrations of valine
